-- LLM evaluation:

  yield full-dag вүЎ "
LEVEL 1: MODULE DEPENDENCY GRAPH (CYCLIC вҖ” not a valid DAG)
  Nodes: mayor, witness, refinery, beads, gt, dolt
  Edges (14):
    dolt вҶҗ beads, mayor, witness, refinery, gt
    beads вҶҗ mayor, gt
    gt вҶҗ mayor, witness, refinery  (BUT gt вҶ’ mayor, gt вҶ’ witness creates cycles)
    mayor вҶҗ witness, gt
    witness вҶҗ gt
    refinery вҶҗ gt
  Cycles: gt вҶ” mayor, gt вҶ’ witness вҶ’ mayor вҶ’ gt
  Partial topological order (ignoring cycles):
    Layer 0: dolt (no dependencies)
    Layer 1: beads (depends only on dolt)
    Layer 2: refinery (depends on gt, dolt вҖ” but gt is in cycle)
    Cycle group: {gt, mayor, witness} вҖ” mutually dependent, cannot be layered

LEVEL 2: SUB-MODULE DEPENDENCY GRAPHS (all acyclic)
  mayor (3 sub-modules, 2 edges):
    Layer 0: dispatcher (sink вҖ” receives from work-planner, escalation-handler)
    Layer 1: work-planner, escalation-handler (both depend on dispatcher)
  witness (3 sub-modules, 2 edges):
    Layer 0: lifecycle-tracker
    Layer 1: health-monitor вҶ’ lifecycle-tracker
    Layer 2: nudge-engine вҶ’ health-monitor
  refinery (3 sub-modules, 2 edges):
    Layer 0: conflict-resolver
    Layer 1: bisect-engine вҶ’ conflict-resolver
    Layer 2: merge-queue вҶ’ bisect-engine
  beads (3 sub-modules, 2 edges):
    Layer 0: issue-store (sink)
    Layer 1: dep-graph, query-engine (both depend on issue-store)
  gt (4 sub-modules, 3 edges):
    Layer 0: dolt-manager, comms-bus (sinks)
    Layer 1: command-router вҶ’ {dolt-manager, comms-bus}
    Layer 2: cli-parser вҶ’ command-router
  dolt (3 sub-modules, 2 edges):
    Layer 0: version-store (sink)
    Layer 1: sql-server, replication (both depend on version-store)
"

  yield layer-count вүЎ 3

  yield total-nodes вүЎ 25

  yield total-edges вүЎ 27

  yield summary вүЎ "The Gas Town dependency graph is NOT a valid DAG at the module level due to cycles involving gt, mayor, and witness. The core issue: gt is an orchestration layer that both depends on and is depended upon by agent modules, creating mutual dependencies. At the sub-module level, all 6 modules have clean acyclic internal structures (19 sub-modules, 13 sub-edges, all DAGs). The consistency check (score 9/10) revealed that the module-level cycles dissolve at the sub-module level вҖ” gt.comms-bus and gt.command-router are distinct sub-modules that handle opposite directions of the cycle. The architecture has a clean foundational layer (dolt вҶ’ beads) and a clean application layer (refinery, mayor, witness sub-modules), but the gt orchestration layer bridges both and creates the cycle. The proposed fix: split gt into gt-cli (pure command interface) and gt-core (coordination logic), which would yield an acyclic graph with 4 clean layers."

