вҠў= obs-cycle-discovery-emergent
  given В§14-dependency-graph-builder
  yield observations вүЎ "EMERGENT CYCLE DETECTION: The program was designed to analyze a DAG, but the Gas Town codebase turned out to have cycles (gt вҶ” mayor, gt вҶ’ witness вҶ’ mayor вҶ’ gt). This is an honest result вҖ” the program didn't force acyclicity, it discovered the actual structure. The handle-cycle guard branch produced genuinely useful architectural analysis: the proposal to split gt into gt-cli and gt-core is a real insight about Gas Town's architecture. This demonstrates that dependency graph analysis programs should ALWAYS include both acyclic and cyclic branches, never assume the answer."

вҠў= obs-wildcard-accumulate-correctness
  given В§14-dependency-graph-builder
  yield observations вүЎ "WILDCARD + ACCUMULATE INTERACTION: Both spawners use `accumulate` mode (explicit default in v0.2). analyzer-*вҶ’depends-on resolved to all 6 analyzer cells and waited for all to freeze before build-adjacency could execute. Similarly, sub-analyzer-*вҶ’sub-modules waited for all 6 sub-analyzer cells. The accumulate semantics are correct for this program: we need ALL modules analyzed before building the adjacency list. Using `replace` would be wrong here because there's no iteration loop over the spawned analyzer cells вҖ” they're one-shot. The explicit `accumulate` keyword makes this intent clear versus R16's implicit default."

вҠў= obs-evolution-loop-sub-consistency
  given В§14-dependency-graph-builder
  yield observations вүЎ "вҠўвҲҳ ON SUB-MODULE ANALYSIS: The refine-graph evolution loop iterated twice. Iteration 1 produced sub-module decompositions that were individually clean (all acyclic) but had a cross-module consistency issue: gt.agent-comms was identified as a bottleneck mediating all inter-agent communication. Iteration 2 refined gt's decomposition to rename agent-comms вҶ’ comms-bus, clarifying its architectural role. The consistency score jumped from 7 to 9. This demonstrates вҠўвҲҳ's value even for structural analysis вҖ” the first pass identifies components, the second pass aligns them with cross-cutting concerns. The sub-analyzer oracles being aspirational under вҠўвҲҳ was important: they guided feedback without blocking the first iteration."

вҠў= obs-two-level-graph-structure
  given В§14-dependency-graph-builder
  yield observations вүЎ "TWO-LEVEL DECOMPOSITION REVEALS HIDDEN STRUCTURE: The module-level graph has cycles, but the sub-module-level graphs are all acyclic. This is a genuine architectural insight: the cycles are an artifact of module-level granularity. At the sub-module level, the bidirectional mayorвҶ”gt relationship is actually two distinct unidirectional paths through different sub-modules (mayor.dispatcher вҶ’ gt.comms-bus for commands, gt.command-router вҶ’ mayor.escalation-handler for routing). The two-level analysis is strictly more informative than single-level вҖ” it distinguishes 'real' architectural cycles from 'apparent' cycles caused by coarse-grained module boundaries. 25 total nodes across 6 modules, 27 total edges across both levels."

вҠў= obs-bottom-propagation-clean
  given В§14-dependency-graph-builder
  yield observations вүЎ "вҠҘ PROPAGATION VIA GUARD CLAUSES [v0.2]: handle-acyclic was skipped by its guard clause, producing ordering-summary вүЎ вҠҘ and dag-status вүЎ вҠҘ. assemble-full-graph declared `given? handle-acyclicвҶ’ordering-summary` (optional given), accepting the вҠҘ and proceeding with only handle-cycleвҶ’cycle-analysis. The вҲҙ body correctly handled this: 'If handle-acyclicвҶ’ordering-summary is available, incorporate it.' Since it was вҠҘ, the LLM used the cycle analysis instead. This is the v0.2 pattern for conditional data flow: guard вҶ’ skip вҶ’ вҠҘ вҶ’ given? вҶ’ graceful degradation. No wasted LLM calls on the irrelevant acyclic branch."

вҠў= obs-spawner-template-interaction
  given В§14-dependency-graph-builder
  yield observations вүЎ "DOUBLE SPAWNER PATTERN: This program uses two вҠўвҠў spawners (spawn-dependency-analyzers and spawn-sub-module-analyzers) with two В§-templates (dependency-analyzer-template and sub-module-analyzer-template). Each spawner produces exactly one cell per module (6 each). The templates are never directly evaluated вҖ” they serve as blueprints. This is the most spawner-intensive program in the R17 corpus: 12 cells spawned total (6+6). The wildcard deps (analyzer-*вҶ’field and sub-analyzer-*вҶ’field) correctly collected outputs from both sets independently. The naming convention (analyzer-{module-name} and sub-analyzer-{module-name}) made wildcard resolution unambiguous."

вҠў= obs-file-scope-recovery-unused
  given В§14-dependency-graph-builder
  yield observations вүЎ "FILE-SCOPE вҠЁ? NEVER TRIGGERED: The file-scope recovery policy (retry max 2, then error-value(вҠҘ)) was never activated across all 23 frames. validate-acyclicity also has its own cell-level вҠЁ? (retry max 2), which takes precedence over the file-scope policy вҖ” but it too was never triggered. All oracles passed on first attempt. The most likely trigger in a real execution would be the structural oracles on sub-module analyzers (вҠЁ sub-edges only reference sub-modules within this module) вҖ” an LLM could easily hallucinate a cross-module edge. Under вҠўвҲҳ, those oracles are aspirational, so the failure would feed into check-sub-consistency as a conflict rather than blocking. The вҠЁ? safety net's value is in error containment, not error prevention."
